# Lockfiles are deliberately COMMITTED — they pin exact dependency
# versions so Docker builds and CI install the same tree every time.
# Apps ship lockfiles; only published libraries omit them. Keep these
# tracked. (If a teammate adds yarn.lock or package-lock.json by mistake,
# delete the file rather than re-ignoring it — pnpm is the canonical
# package manager for this repo.)

# Contracts
contracts/artifacts/
contracts/cache/
contracts/typechain-types/
contracts/deployments/

# Persistent host bind-mount for the api service. Holds encrypted agent
# secrets (agent-secrets.json) + SQLite (api.db). NEVER commit — the file
# is AES-GCM encrypted under MASTER_KEY but exposing both wastes the
# encryption boundary. Keep .gitkeep tracked so a fresh checkout still
# has the directory present (compose creates it implicitly otherwise,
# but explicit .gitkeep avoids surprises on Windows).
data/*
!data/.gitkeep
